      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ci): guard dependency graph changes in PRs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Replaces the inline dependency-awareness workflow logic with a checked-in Node script that runs from the trusted base checkout under `pull_request_target`.\n- Labels and comments only for actual dependency graph surfaces: package lockfiles, workspace/patch dependency policy files, or `package.json` `dependencies`/`devDependencies` field changes.\n- Hard-fails package lockfile and dependency/devDependency manifest changes unless `@openclaw/openclaw-secops` authorizes the current guard state with `/allow-dependencies-change`.\n- Keeps `dependencies-changed` as the only dependency label; the hard block is the failing check plus the guard comment.\n- Adds secops ownership for the guard and focused workflow/script tests.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Script-only or metadata-only `package.json` changes do not get the dependency label and do not block.\n- `/allow-dependencies-change` is only a comment token consumed on the next workflow run or manual re-run. It does not trigger an action or add labels by itself.\n- The override records the current head SHA when accepted. After authorization, a later push requires a fresh `/allow-dependencies-change` comment.\n- This PR adds the failing check behavior, but repository rulesets/branch protection still need to require the `Dependency Change Awareness` check before it becomes an enforced merge gate.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.scripts.json scripts/github/dependency-change-awareness.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-script.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check -- scripts/github/dependency-change-awareness.mjs scripts/sync-openclaw-label-colors.mjs test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-script.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts`\n",
